Microsoft Dynamics CRM Consultant Reading 3 month contract £595 per day
As the Microsoft Dynamics CRM Consultant, you will consult on, design, configure, customise, develop and implement solutions on the Microsoft Dynamics 365 platforms to agreed timescales and budget.
Result areas: •Delivery of new solutions and upgraded solutions on the Microsoft Dynamics 365 platform - both online and on premise •Delivery of new solutions on the Dynamics 365 portals from Microsoft/Microsoft Open Source Portals •Undertake consulting and development activities including planning, estimating, design, creation, testing, data migration, documentation and the release of Dynamics 365 and portal implementations; •Effectively work in 'time-boxed' sprints, with adaptive planning from a prioritised work list, and in a test-driven manner; •Active participation in project planning, daily stand-up meetings, reviews, retrospectives, sprint and release planning, demos and other meetings; •Adhere to, proactively maintain and improve agreed practices, procedures, quality and development standards; •Carry out estimation of effort for development activities; •Carry out timely and effective resolutions to development issues; •Undertake code reviews and ensure procedures are adhered to; •Contribute to customer meetings and workshops and produce checkpoint reports as agreed;
Knowledge and Qualifications: •Good class degree in Computing/Information Technology (eg BSc, minimum 2:1) or equivalent; •Good working knowledge of agile software development and test-driven development methodologies; •Strong working knowledge of the MS Dynamics 365/2016/15/13/11 SDK and C#; •Good knowledge of application development, using the MS Dynamics 365/2016/15/13/11 SDK, C#, SSRS, SSRS; •Knowledge of customising and extending Microsoft Dynamics CRM, in particular plug-ins and workflows; •Good knowledge of business processes; •Good working knowledge of version control methods and software such as Team Foundation Server or Visual Studio Team Services, Azure DevOps; •Microsoft Dynamics certification desirable (Microsoft Certified IT Professional);
Please apply below to be considered.
Capita IT Resourcing is acting as an Employment Business in relation to this vacancy.
